"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Deep Dive: Why Cursor CLI E2E Tests Are Flaky\n\n## Context\n\nCI run [22831463580](https://github.com/entireio/cli/actions/runs/22831463580) (commit `a258927d`) shows 2/42 cursor-cli tests failing: `TestPartialStaging` and `TestUserSplitsAgentChanges`. Additionally, the current branch HEAD (`e90e3f9c`) reverted the per-session config isolation fix, meaning the ENOENT race condition is also unfixed.\n\nThere are **two independent flakiness sources** for cursor-cli:\n\n---\n\n## Finding 1: Premature WaitFor Settle (Root Cause of CI Failures)\n\n### Evidence\n\n**TestPartialStaging** — second prompt produced no file changes:\n- `split_commits_test.go:89`: `git commit -m Add goodbye world failed: exit status 1` — \"nothing added to commit\"\n- Console shows agent started, displayed \"Claude 4.6 Opus (Thinking)\" + status bar `/ commands · @ files · ! shell`, but never produced output\n- `RunPrompt` returned **without error** (no timeout), meaning WaitFor matched and settled\n\n**TestUserSplitsAgentChanges** — agent created zero files:\n- `split_commits_test.go:27-28`: `expected files matching docs/c.md` / `docs/d.md` — empty\n- Same pattern: agent showed \"Thinking\" + `/ commands` status bar, then WaitFor settled\n\n### Root Cause\n\nThe Cursor CLI's TUI **always shows `/ commands` in the status bar**, including during the \"Thinking\" phase. The WaitFor mechanism:\n\n1. Matches `/ commands` pattern against full pane content (line 138 of tmux.go)\n2. Checks content changed since Send (it did — prompt was echoed)\n3. Waits for 2 seconds of stable content (`settleTime = 2 * time.Second`)\n4. Returns success\n\n**The problem**: When the model takes >2 seconds to start producing visible output after \"Thinking\" starts, the pane content is stable (nothing is changing visually), and WaitFor settles on the stale `/ commands` text. The test thinks the agent finished, but it's still thinking.\n\nThis explains why 40/42 tests pass — most of the time the model responds fast enough that the content keeps changing (file edits, response text), preventing premature settle.\n\n### Fix: Use Completion-Specific Pattern\n\n**File**: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\n\nChange the completion WaitFor in `RunPrompt` (line 113) from:\n```go\ncontent, waitErr := s.WaitFor(a.PromptPattern(), timeout)\n```\nto:\n```go\ncontent, waitErr := s.WaitFor(`Add a follow-up`, timeout)\n```\n\nThe `Add a follow-up` text only appears in Cursor's input box **after** the agent finishes processing a prompt. It does NOT appear during the \"Thinking\" phase.\n\nKeep `PromptPattern()` as `/ commands` for initial startup detection (used in `acceptTrustDialogIfNeeded` and the startup WaitFor).\n\nSimilarly update `StartSession`'s `SendPrompt` flow if it exists, and the `Session` `WaitForReady` pattern.\n\n---\n\n## Finding 2: ENOENT Config Race (Reverted Fix)\n\n### Evidence\n\nThe current HEAD (`e90e3f9c`) reverted commit `a258927d` which isolated each cursor session's config directory. Without isolation, parallel cursor sessions write to the shared `~/.config/cursor/cli-config.json` via atomic temp-file rename, causing ENOENT crashes.\n\n### Fix: Re-apply Config Isolation\n\n**File**: `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`\n\nRe-implement `cursorConfigDir()` from commit `a258927d`:\n- Create unique temp dir per session: `/tmp/cursor-e2e-config-<random>/`\n- Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` and `HOME` to this directory\n- Pre-seed `cursor/cli-config.json` with `{}`\n- Register cleanup via `s.OnClose()`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go` | Change completion WaitFor pattern to `Add a follow-up`; re-add `cursorConfigDir()` per-session isolation |\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\n2. `mise run test:e2e:canary` — Vogon canary must pass\n3. `mise run test:e2e --agent cursor-cli` — full cursor-cli suite (requires user approval due to API costs)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from be